    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jc.00275_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">New York,</name>
                    <date when="1876-04-19">Ap'l 19, 1876.<ptr target="loc.01937_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Mr. Walt Whitman,</salute>
                <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I do not forget what I am owing to you, and try in every way to raise <hi rend="underline">something</hi> towards 
                discharging my obligation to you. But I have been losing, instead of gaining, for some time. I know that sometime 
                I shall have a good business, but that don't help matters for the present. In order to tide over the dullness, I 
                have accepted proofreading outside of my business, <choice><abbr>altho'</abbr><expan>although</expan></choice>
                forbidden to do so by <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#me">oculists</unclear>. 
                Without being asked, you may be certain I shall send if but a small amount <hi rend="underline">as soon as I can</hi>. 
                You would be surprised if you knew 
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_jc.00276_large.jpg" type="verso"/> 
                exactly what I have had to contend with in the way of obstacles for some time. I am occupied at proofreading from 
                7:30 A.M. till 5:30 P.M., with only a &#189; hr. for lunch at noon. My business is in the hands of a rural boy, &#38; 
                I attend to my correspondence from 4 A.M. till 6:30 A.M. &#38; from 7:30 to 10 P.M. &#38; sometimes later, and Sundays. 
                I can still do nothing but ask for your indulgence. But my mortification at having to ask you to wait, under all the 
                circumstances, is very great. Sometime I hope to make amends and a personal explanation.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>In great haste,</salute>
                <salute>Yours truly,</salute>
                <signed>C. P Somerby</signed>
            </closer>
